@startuml
title Employee Creates "test" Product and Sells 1 Unit

actor Employee
participant IMS
participant ProductClass
participant BillClass
database Database
entity FileSystem

== Create Product ==

Employee -> IMS : Clicks "Products"
IMS -> ProductClass : Open product form

Employee -> ProductClass : Enters product details:\nCategory: Test Category, Supplier: Test Supplier\nName: Test Product, Price: 10, Qty: 100, Status: Active
Employee -> ProductClass : Clicks "Save"

ProductClass -> Database : Check if the product exists in the database
Database --> ProductClass : Not found

ProductClass -> Database : Insert Test Product
Database --> ProductClass : OK

ProductClass --> Employee : "Product Added Successfully"

== Sell 1 Unit ==

Employee -> BillClass : Opens billing form

BillClass -> Database : Load active products
Database --> BillClass : Product list

Employee -> BillClass : Selects Test Product from product list

Employee -> BillClass : Enters customer details:\nName: Test Customer, Contact No.: 123

Employee -> BillClass : Sets "Quantity" to 1 and clicks "Add|Update"
BillClass -> BillClass : Add to cart, calculate totals:\nAmount: 1, Discount: 5%, Net Pay: 9.5

Employee -> BillClass : Clicks "Generate Bill"

BillClass -> BillClass : Builds bill
BillClass -> Database : Update Test Product quantity from 100 to 99
Database --> BillClass : OK

BillClass -> FileSystem : Save bill to file
BillClass --> Employee : "Bill has been generated"

Employee -> BillClass : Clicks "Print"
BillClass -> FileSystem : Send bill to printer
BillClass --> Employee : Print dialog opens

@enduml